about.summary: Summarizes key information about statistical objects in tidy tibbles. This makes it easy to report results, create plots and consistently work with large numbers of models at once. Broom provides three verbs that each provide different types of information about a model. tidy() summarizes information about model components such as coefficients of a regression. glance() reports information about an entire model, such as goodness of fit measures like AIC and BIC. augment() adds information about individual observations to a dataset, such as fitted values or influence measures.

name: r-broom
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set version = "0.5.6" %}
{% set posix = 'm2-' if win else '' %}
{% set native = 'm2w64-' if win else '' %}

package:
  name: r-broom
  version: {{ version|replace("-", "_") }}

source:
  url:
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/broom_{{ version }}.tar.gz
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/Archive/broom/broom_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 0b06f670ace7349b95a71313c360dbded2428d65d17eaacccc93750196964335

build:
  merge_build_host: true  # [win]
  number: 1
  noarch: generic
  rpaths:
    - lib/R/lib/
    - lib/

requirements:
  build:
    - {{ posix }}zip               # [win]
  host:
    - r-base
    - r-backports
    - r-dplyr
    - r-generics >=0.0.2
    - r-nlme
    - r-purrr
    - r-reshape2
    - r-stringr
    - r-tibble
    - r-tidyr
  run:
    - r-base
    - r-backports
    - r-dplyr
    - r-generics >=0.0.2
    - r-nlme
    - r-purrr
    - r-reshape2
    - r-stringr
    - r-tibble
    - r-tidyr

test:
  commands:
    - $R -e "library('broom')"           # [not win]
    - "\"%R%\" -e \"library('broom')\""  # [win]

about:
  home: http://github.com/tidyverse/broom
  license: MIT
  license_file: LICENSE
  summary: Summarizes key information about statistical objects in tidy tibbles. This makes it easy to report results, create plots and consistently work with large
    numbers of models at once. Broom provides three verbs that each provide different types of information about a model. tidy() summarizes information about model
    components such as coefficients of a regression. glance() reports information about an entire model, such as goodness of fit measures like AIC and BIC. augment()
    adds information about individual observations to a dataset, such as fitted values or influence measures.
  license_family: MIT

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - conda-forge/r
